	&lt;li&gt;Candela is the SI unit of luminous intensity, which measures the amount of light emitted per second in a particular direction.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Mole is the SI unit of amount of substance, which measures the number of elementary entities (such as atoms, molecules, ions, etc.) in a given sample of matter.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Watt is the SI unit of power, which measures the rate of energy transfer or conversion per unit time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

