&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Endemic species&lt;/strong&gt; are unique to a particular area and are not found anywhere else in the world.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These species are important because they often play a critical role in the ecosystem of their native habitat.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Endemic species are often at risk of extinction because they are vulnerable to changes in their environment and are not adapted to survive in other areas.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Conservation efforts are important to protect these species and preserve their unique genetic and ecological heritage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Endangered species are those that are at risk of becoming extinct in the near future. This can be due to habitat loss, poaching, climate change, or other factors.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Threatened species are those that are likely to become endangered in the future if conservation measures are not taken.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Critically endangered species are those that are at an extremely high risk of becoming extinct in the near future. Conservation efforts are urgently needed to save these species.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Endemic species are those species of plants and animals which are found exclusively in a particular area. This statement is true and accurately describes what endemic species are.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

